        <page n="02" image="va.au.ss.1859.10.04.02">
            <div type="a">
                <column>1</column>
                <head>The Democratic Imbroglio</head>
                <origin/>
                <excerpt>"With the great enemy thus divided and engaged in a fierce internecine war,
                    may we not hope for the cordial union of the conservative opposition, upon a
                    national platform, which ignores all issues that are not of practical interest
                    to the country."</excerpt>
                <transcript/>
                <trailer/>
                <commentary/>
                <names/>
                <summary>Explains how the Democratic party is divided over popular sovereignty and
                    Stephen Douglas. This affords the Opposition a great opportunity, and they may
                    even pick up some disaffected Democrats.</summary>
            </div>
